    "Specific applications of these optimization methods for object detection and recognition in traffic scenes are shown in Table 3.",
    "Data AugmentationData augmentation' refers to a technique used to expand the dataset required for a deep learning model by generating variants of existing real-world images to increase the size of the required dataset.",
    "Therefore, training with a large amount of data is crucial for the optimal performance of any deep-learning model [44].",
    "Data enhancement techniques can be broadly classified into the following categories: geometric transformation-based techniques, color transformation-based techniques, stochastic occlusion-based techniques, and deep learning-based techniques.",
    "Geometric transformations typically change the pixel positions of the images in the training dataset, including rotation, scaling, flipping, cropping, filling, translation, and affine transformations."
